data.title: Movie Review: Inseminoid (1981)
data.meta_description: Based on the title and the poster, I was expecting some real garbage. Like David DeCoteau levels of garbage. But it turns out this is a real movie. It’s not necessarily great, but it tries. I guess…
data.text:
Based on the title and the poster, I was expecting some real garbage. Like David DeCoteau levels of garbage. But it turns out this is a real movie. It’s not necessarily great, but it tries.

I guess I’d consider it an Alien knockoff. It is from 1981, just two years after the release of Ridley Scott’s film. And it involves an alien basically raping a woman.

It’s sort of disturbing, but I suppose it goes without saying that it’s inferior to Alien. It’s not as monster-heavy, likely because of budgetary restrictions. Instead of a xenomorph, we have a woman going around killing people, and that’s where I lose a bit of interest.

Rating: 5/10
